#include <string.h>
int isPalindrome(char* str) {
    int left = 0, right = strlen(str) - 1;
    while (left < right) {
        if (str[left] != str[right])
            return 0;
        left++;
        right--;
    }
    return 1;
}
```
Two-pointer approach: compare characters from both ends moving inward. If all pairs match, it's a palindrome. Time: O(n), Space: O(1). Examples: 'racecar' → yes, 'hello' → no.

