#include <ctype.h>
void countVC(char* str, int* vowels, int* consonants) {
    *vowels = 0;
    *consonants = 0;
    for (int i = 0; str[i]; i++) {
        char c = tolower(str[i]);
        if (c >= 'a' && c <= 'z') {
            if (c == 'a' || c == 'e' || c == 'i' || c == 'o' || c == 'u')
                (*vowels)++;
            else
                (*consonants)++;
        }
    }
}
```
Convert to lowercase for case-insensitive comparison. Check if character is alphabetic first, then classify as vowel or consonant. Ignore non-alphabetic characters.

